thought:
**Analysis of Administrative Changes in Long An Province**

Okay, I'm tasked with determining the new administrative unit for the address "Xã Thái Bình Trung, Huyện Vĩnh Hưng, Tỉnh Long An." My first step is to confirm if "Tỉnh Long An" has undergone any mergers. I checked `60-NQ/TW` and found that Long An was indeed merged with Tây Ninh, forming the new province "Tỉnh Tây Ninh."

Now, I need to pinpoint the fate of "Thái Bình Trung." I'll scrutinize the available resolutions, particularly focusing on those related to Tây Ninh. Scanning the "Other resolutions," I identified `1682/NQ-UBTVQH15` as the relevant document concerning administrative adjustments in Tây Ninh.

Within `1682/NQ-UBTVQH15`, I found three key sections concerning "Thái Bình Trung." It appears the former "Xã Thái Bình Trung" has been split into pieces.
First, a part of it, along with other communes, is merged to form the new commune: "xã Tuyên Bình".
Second, a part of it, along with other communes, is merged to form the new commune: "xã Vĩnh Hưng".
Finally, the remaining piece of "Thái Bình Trung" will be merged to form the new commune: "xã Khánh Hưng".

Thus, I've identified three candidate new wards: "xã Tuyên Bình", "xã Vĩnh Hưng", and "xã Khánh Hưng", all within the new province "Tỉnh Tây Ninh." The original "Thái Bình Trung" has been completely re-organized.

To resolve the address, the user will need more information regarding the exact part of "Thái Bình Trung".
